# Module Purpose

Responsibilities:

- Admin Dashboard
- User Management
- Order Monitoring
- Withdrawal Management
- System Configuration
- Audit Logs
- Business Monitoring

Admin Module is the operational control center of the platform.

---

# MVP Scope

Admin can:

✓ View Users

✓ View Orders

✓ View Withdrawals

✓ Approve Withdrawals

✓ Reject Withdrawals

✓ Complete Withdrawals

✓ View Dashboard Statistics

✓ View Audit Logs

---

Admin cannot:

✗ Modify commissions manually

✗ Modify order ownership

✗ Delete financial records

✗ Delete audit logs

---

# Authorization Rules

All Admin endpoints require:

```csharp
[Authorize(Roles = nameof(UserRole.Admin))]
```

Never trust:

- Frontend role
- Request body role
- Query string role

Always validate from JWT.

---

# Admin Dashboard

Purpose:

Provide operational overview.

---

Dashboard Metrics

Users

- Total Users
- New Users Today
- Active Users

Orders

- Total Orders
- Pending Orders
- Approved Orders
- Rejected Orders

Cashback

- Total Cashback Paid
- Pending Cashback

Withdrawals

- Pending Withdrawals
- Completed Withdrawals
- Total Withdrawn

System

- Total Affiliate Links Generated

---

Dashboard data must come from database queries.

Never calculate metrics in frontend.

---

# User Management Rules

Admin may:

- View User Details
- Search Users
- Filter Users
- Suspend Users
- Reactivate Users

---

Admin may NOT:

- Delete Users
- Modify Balances Directly
- Change User Ownership

---

# User Status Rules

Allowed Actions

Active

↓

Suspended

↓

Active

---

Deleted status should not be used in MVP.

---

Suspended users:

Cannot Login

Cannot Generate Links

Cannot Create Withdrawals

---

# User Search Rules

Support:

- Email
- UserId
- Name

---

Always paginate results.

Never load all users.

---

# Orders Management Rules

Admin may:

- View Orders
- Filter Orders
- Search Orders

---

Admin may NOT:

- Create Orders
- Delete Orders
- Change Order Ownership

---

Admin may NOT manually approve commissions.

Commission source remains provider data.

---

# Withdrawal Management Rules

Admin may:

- View Requests
- Approve Requests
- Reject Requests
- Complete Requests

---

All actions must create audit logs.

---

Approval flow

Pending

↓

Approved

↓

Completed

---

Rejection flow

Pending

↓

Rejected

---

Status transitions must follow withdrawal rules.

---

# System Settings Rules

System settings must be configurable.

Examples:

Cashback Percentage

Minimum Withdrawal

Maximum Withdrawal

Campaign Id

Provider Settings

---

Do NOT hardcode business configuration.

---

Suggested Entity

SystemSetting

Fields:

- Key
- Value
- Description
- UpdatedAt

---

# Audit Log Rules

Critical Requirement

Every admin action must be auditable.

---

Suggested Entity

AuditLog

Fields:

- Id
- UserId
- Action
- EntityType
- EntityId
- OldValue
- NewValue
- CreatedAt

---

Examples

Withdrawal Approved

Withdrawal Rejected

User Suspended

System Setting Changed

---

Audit logs must be append-only.

Never update logs.

Never delete logs.

---

# Financial Safety Rules

Admin actions affecting money must be logged.

Examples

Withdrawal Approval

Withdrawal Rejection

Withdrawal Completion

Balance Adjustment

---

Audit trail is mandatory.

---

# Manual Balance Adjustment Rules

Not supported in MVP.

---

Future implementation:

BalanceAdjustmentRequest

with approval workflow.

---

Never directly update user balance from admin screens.

---

# Reporting Rules

Admin reports are read-only.

Examples

Revenue Reports

Cashback Reports

Withdrawal Reports

---

Reports must not modify data.

---

# Search & Filtering Rules

Users

- Email
- Status
- Created Date

Orders

- Status
- Date Range

Withdrawals

- Status
- Date Range

---

Always use server-side filtering.

---

# Frontend Rules

Admin Area

Separate from user area.

Suggested routes:

```text
/admin
/admin/users
/admin/orders
/admin/withdrawals
/admin/settings
/admin/audit-logs
```

---

Admin pages must:

- Require Admin Role
- Redirect unauthorized users

---

Frontend must not:

- Decide permissions
- Hide-only security controls

Backend remains source of truth.

